Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat(float):=20pin-to-top=20=E2=80=94=20true=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?always-on-top=20via=20Document=20PiP=20handoff?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Document PiP is blocked in side panels but the float popup IS a tab
context, so it can call documentPictureInPicture.requestWindow itself.

- Pin button in the float header: hands the chat off to a genuine
  always-on-top PiP window (floats above ALL apps), clones styles,
  minimizes the owning popup (PiP dies with its opener, so it must
  stay alive)
- Unpin (button in either window, or closing the PiP) returns the chat
  to the popup and restores/focuses it
- placeholder screen in the popup while pinned explains the state
- feature-detected: the pin button only appears where Document PiP
  exists (e.g. hidden if Brave ships without it)
---
 apps/extension/entrypoints/pip/main.tsx | 152 +++++++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 149 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

